#!CDarkGreen #!N  #!Rimwinom Image 
Window Options Menu #!N #!EC #!N #!N The  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Options #!EF 
menu provides the following options, which are available only when the 
Image tool is used in a visual program: #!N #!I0 #!N 
#!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   View Control ... #!EF #!I50 #!N Opens 
a dialog box with various view control options. For more information 
on this menu option, see  #!Lchav,dxall300 h Controlling the Image: View Control...  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Undo #!EF #!I50 #!N Returns to the view of the image 
that was displayed before the most recent action (effectively undoing the 
action). See  #!Lrestimg,dxall318 h Restoring Images  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Redo #!EF #!I50 
#!N Restores the view of the image that was displayed before 
the last  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Undo #!EF action. See  #!Lrestimg,dxall318 h Restoring Images  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 
#!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Reset #!EF #!I50 #!N Resets the camera to its 
initial position and direction. See  #!Lrestimg,dxall318 h Restoring Images  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
AutoAxes... #!EF #!I50 #!N Places axes around the image the next 
time you execute the visual program. See  #!Lgautax,dxall324 h AutoAxes...  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 
#!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Set Background Color... #!EF #!I50 #!N Sets the background 
color of the image. See  #!Lstbkcl,dxall325 h Set Background Color...  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Display Rotation Globe #!EF #!I50 #!N Enables and disables the wire-framed 
globe display in many of the view control options. While the 
toggle button is pressed in, the globe display is enabled. See 
 #!Lrotobj,dxall305 h Rotating the Object  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Rendering Options... #!EF #!I50 #!N 
Displays a dialog box, allowing you to choose hardware or software 
rendering options. See  #!Lglopt,dxall327 h Rendering Options...  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Image Depth 
#!EF #!I50 #!N Specifies the number of bits (8, 12 or 
24) per color. See  #!Limdep,dxall328 h Image Depth  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Throttle... 
#!EF #!I50 #!N Specifies the minimum number of seconds to display 
each frame. See  #!Lspeed,dxall329 h Changing the Rate of Frame Display: Throttle...  #!EL  . #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Change Image 
Name... #!EF #!I50 #!N Opens a dialog box in that you 
can specify a new title for the Image window. See  #!Lchtiiw,dxall330 h Changing the Title of an Image Window  #!EL  
. #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Control Panel Access... #!EF #!I50 #!N 
Allows you to specify which control panels and control panel groups 
are accessible from the Image Window's  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Open All Control Panels 
#!EF option under the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Windows #!EF menu. See  #!Lcpacc,dxall331 h Control Panel Access...  #!EL  . 
#!I0 #!N #!N #!N #!N #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-i-normal--18*   Next Topic #!EF #!N 
